1 damages resulting from any negligent or willful acts involving the use of the firearm while it is
2 owned by the person. No firearm shall be transferred in this State unless the transferee at the time
3 of the transfer provides proof that the transferee has complied with the provisions of this section.
4 (b) For purposes of this section, a person is deemed to own a firearm if the firearm is lost
5 or stolen until the loss or theft is reported pursuant to G.S. 14-409.13.
6 (c) Any person who owns a firearm on December 1, 2025, shall obtain the insurance
7 required by this section by January 15, 2026.
8 (d) This section does not apply to any law enforcement officer authorized to carry a
9 firearm.
10 (e) The Department of Insurance shall adopt rules to implement this section."
11 SECTION 8.(c) Subsection (a) of this section is effective when it becomes law and
12 applies to permit applications received on or after that date.
