32 PART XV. PROHIBIT THE SALE OR POSSESSION OF GHOST GUNS
33 SECTION 15.(a) Article 52A of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes is amended by
34 adding a new section to read:
35 "§ 14-409B. Ghost guns prohibited.
36 (a) Definition. – For purposes of this section, the term "ghost gun" means a firearm,
37 including a frame or receiver, that lacks a unique serial number engraved or cased in metal alloy
38 on the frame or receiver by a licensed manufacturer, maker, or importer under federal law or
39 markings in accordance with 27 C.F.R. § 479.102. This term does not include a firearm that has
40 been rendered permanently inoperable or a firearm that is not required to have a serial number in
41 accordance with the federal Gun Control Act of 1968.
42 (b) Prohibition. – It shall be unlawful for any person, firm, or corporation to manufacture,
43 sell, give away, transfer, use, or possess a ghost gun.
44 (c) Punishment. – Any person violating this section is guilty of a Class I felony."
45 SECTION 15.(b) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to
46 offenses committed on or after that date.
