9 SECTION 19.(d) G.S. 50B-3.1(d) reads as rewritten:
10 "(d) Surrender. – Upon service of the order, the defendant shall immediately surrender to
11 the sheriff possession of all firearms, machine guns, ammunition, permits to purchase firearms,
12 and permits to carry concealed firearms that are in the care, custody, possession, ownership, or
13 control of the defendant. In the event that weapons cannot be surrendered at the time the order is
14 served, the defendant shall surrender the firearms, ammunitions, and permits to the sheriff within
15 24 hours of service at a time and place specified by the sheriff. If the defendant fails to surrender
16 the firearms, ammunitions, and permits to the sheriff within 24 hours of service, the court shall
17 order the sheriff to seize the firearms, ammunitions, and permits. The sheriff shall store the
18 firearms or contract with a licensed firearms dealer to provide storage.
19 (1) If the court orders the defendant to surrender firearms, ammunition, and
20 permits, the court shall inform the plaintiff and the defendant of the terms of
21 the protective order and include these terms on the face of the order, including
22 that the defendant is prohibited from possessing, purchasing, or receiving or
23 attempting to possess, purchase, or receive a firearm for so long as the
24 protective order or any successive protective order is in effect. The terms of
25 the order shall include instructions as to how the defendant may request
26 retrieval of any firearms, ammunition, and permits surrendered to the sheriff
27 when the protective order is no longer in effect. The terms shall also include
28 notice of the penalty for violation of G.S. 14-269.8.
29 (2) The sheriff may charge the defendant a reasonable fee for the storage of any
30 firearms and ammunition taken pursuant to a protective order. The fees are
31 payable to the sheriff. The sheriff shall transmit the proceeds of these fees to
32 the county finance officer. The fees shall be used by the sheriff to pay the costs
33 of administering this section and for other law enforcement purposes. The
34 county shall expend the restricted funds for these purposes only. The sheriff
35 shall not release firearms, ammunition, or permits without a court order
36 granting the release. The defendant must remit all fees owed prior to the
37 authorized return of any firearms, ammunition, or permits. The sheriff shall
38 not incur any civil or criminal liability for alleged damage or deterioration due
39 to storage or transportation of any firearms or ammunition held pursuant to
40 this section."
41 SECTION 19.(e) Subsections (a) through (c) of this section become effective
42 October 1, 2025. The remainder of this section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
43 orders issued on or after that date.
